# Exercise 002 - Enabling a public key on a ssh host

1) Generate a local ssh keypair;

2) Copy the contents of your local public key;

3) Log into the remote machine with the credentials you own;

4) Check if the ssh folder exists, if not, create it;

5) Create the authorized keys file and copy your public key in it;

6) Log out from the remote server;

7) Try to login again on the remote server, you should be able to do that
   without typing any password;

8) Logout and then login again after incrementing the verbose level of the ssh
   command and check when the public key evaluation is made;
